EC2

Elastic Compute Cloud

- Is a part of Amazon cloud computing platform, that allows users to rent virtual 
computers on which to run their own computer applications.

Use Cases
- Run cloud-native and enterprise applications
- Scale for HPC applications
- Develop for Apple platforms
- Train and deploy ML applications

How Amazon EC2 works

1. Launch
- Launch an instance by selecting a template with basic config like OS, application
server or applications, instance type.

2. Connect
- Connect to the instance

3. Use
- After connecting, you can begin using it by running commands to install software,
add storage, copy and organize files.


